Package fr.apteryx.imageio.dicom

Interface Summary
BasicWorklistManagementSCPListener An Object implementing BasicWorklistManagementSCPListener is the user-contributed part of a Basic Worklist Management SCP.
ExceptionListener Interface used to be notified of network exceptions when acting as an SCP.
QueryRetrieveSCPListener An Object implementing QueryRetrieveSCPListener is the user-contributed part of a Query/Retrieve SCP or Hanging Protocol Query/Retrieve SCP.
ReceivedObjectListener Interface for use by the Storage SCP when in asynchronous listening mode, that allows more control over the store response sent back to the SCU than StorageSCPListener.
StorageCommitmentRequestListener Interface for listeners of incoming storage commitment requests.
StorageSCPListener Simple interface for use by the Storage SCP when in asynchronous listening mode.
 

Class Summary
AERegistry A registry for Application Entities.
BasicWorklistManagementSCP Implements a Basic Worklist Management SCP together with a user supplied BasicWorklistManagementSCPListener implementation.
BasicWorklistManagementSCU Implements a Basic Worklist Management SCU.
DataElement DataElement is the class of the values stored in DataSet.
DataSet A DICOM data set.
DateRange A range of dates between 2 date-time inclusive.
Day A Date without the time components.
DayRange A range of dates between 2 days inclusive.
DicomMetadata Contains all dicom data elements of a DICOM object being read or written.
DicomReader The DICOM decoder.
DicomReaderSpi The service provider interface for the DICOM reader.
DicomWriter The Dicom encoder.
DicomWriterSpi The service provider interface for the DICOM writer.
Dictionary The registry of all standard DICOM data elements.
FileSet File set read from or to be written to a DICOMDIR file.
FloatingDate A Date that was created without time zone information, and so should not show time zone when written to a DICOM DT (DateTime) data element.
HangingProtocolQueryRetrieveSCP Implements a Hanging Procol Query/Retrieve SCP together with a user supplied QueryRetrieveSCPListener implementation.
HangingProtocolQueryRetrieveSCU Implements a Hanging Protocol Query/Retrieve SCU.
Identifier Identifiers are used by the Query/Retrieve, Basic Worklist Management and Hanging Protocol Query/Retrieve Service Classes.
PeerAE Represents the information needed to connect to a peer DICOM application entity using TCP/IP.
PersonName A DICOM person name.
Plugin Plugin-wide configuration.
QueryRetrieveSCP Implements a Query/Retrieve SCP together with a user supplied QueryRetrieveSCPListener implementation.
QueryRetrieveSCU Implements a Query/Retrieve SCU to access a remote image database.
RawValues Instances of this class are used as arguments of setRawValues methods to specify if the value of read data elements should be decoded into a high level data type (String, Date, images...) or kept as raw byte[] values.
ReceivedObject DICOM object received by a Storage SCP (C-STORE operation) or a Query/Retrieve SCU (C-GET operation).
SecureTransport An instance of SecureTransport must be specified when defining a peer AE or when listening for incoming associations if secure transport with SSL or TLS is sought.
Server Receives association requests.
StorageCommitmentInformation Instances of this class are used either SCU-side or SCP-side of the Storage Commitment Service Class to either specify the SOP instances which safekeeping is requested or the result of such request.
StorageCommitmentResultReceiver In order for a Storage Commitment SCU to receive a result from an SCP, a subclass of StorageCommitmentResultReceiver must be defined, implementing the listener method resultReceived.
StorageCommitmentSCP Implements a Storage Commitment SCP.
StorageCommitmentSCU Implements a Storage Commitment SCU.
StorageCommitmentSCU.Request  
StorageCommitmentSCU.Result  
StorageSCP Implements a Storage SCP for receiving images through the network.
StorageSCU Implements a Storage SCU to be associated to a peer SCP for sending images through the network.
Tag An abstract class defining constants for the DICOM 2007 standard data elements and some convenient static methods to manipulate tags.
Time A Date without the year-month-day components.
TimeRange A range of dates between 2 times inclusive.
UID An abstract class defining constants for some of the main DICOM unique identifiers and the UID.create() method which can be used to return a new unique identifier.
UnknownValue A special class with a unique instance representing attribute values that could not be decoded because the value representation (VR) was unknown.
VerificationSCU Implements a Verification SCU.
VOIDefaultColorModel Color model used when no VOI LUT is used and when the standard Java color models are not suitable.
VOILUTColorModel A 1-component color model representing a VOI LUT encoded as a true lookup table.
VOIWindowColorModel A 1-component color model representing a VOI LUT encoded as a grayscale window (attributes WindowCenter (0028,1050) and WindowWidth(0028,1051)).
VOIWindowColorModelFloat A 1-component color model representing a VOI LUT encoded as a grayscale window (attributes WindowCenter (0028,1050) and WindowWidth(0028,1051)), in the case where the transfer type is float.
 

Exception Summary
DicomException Thrown when an error occurs during coding or decoding.
